  },
  "kind" : "article",
  "metadata" : {
    "role" : "article",
    "roleHeading" : "Article",
    "title" : "Equilibrium of a Rigid Body"
  },
  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "Overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Distinguish between equilibrium of a particle and equilibrium of a rigid body.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Draw free body diagrams of rigid bodies in equilibrium.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Apply the equations of equilibrium for a rigid body to solve static and dynamic equilibrium problems in",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "engineering mechanics.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Non-Particle-Problems",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Non-Particle Problems",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "So long as the forces do not all act on a single point, the problem is non-particle.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Different-Equilibriums",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Different Equilibriums",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "For a non-particle problem, it is in equilibrium when:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "$\\sum F_x = 0$",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "$\\sum F_y = 0$",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "$\\sum M = 0$",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "These conditions are identical to ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/Notes\/documentation\/Notes\/6.1-Newtons-First-Law#Equilibrium-of-Concurrent-Forces",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", but the",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "difference is that we can have moments in non-particle problems.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "In a particle problem, ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$\\sum M = 0$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " refers to there being ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "no moments",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", since it is not possible to have",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "a moment on a particle. In a rigid body problem, ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$\\sum M = 0$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " refers to the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "net moment",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text" : " being zero,",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "which means there may be moments acting on the body, but they cancel each other out.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Applying-the-Equations-for-Non-Particle-Equilibrium",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Applying the Equations for Non-Particle Equilibrium",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Basically just follow these steps:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Draw the free-body diagram, if one is not provided",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Identify the unknown forces. Refer to ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "identifier" : "doc:\/\/Notes\/documentation\/Notes\/5-Newtons-Third-Law#Supports",
                      "isActive" : true,
                      "type" : "reference"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " for the forces acting on",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "certain types of mechanical supports.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "For unknown forces that are not on an axis, resolve them into their x and y components",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Equate the forces in the x and y directions",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Equate the moments about a point",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Solve the equations simultaneously to find the unknown forces",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "orderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "If there are a lot of unknown forces from supports (eg. pivots), consider setting one of them as the pivot",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "and calculate forces as moments about that point.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
  ],
